{
  "stem": "9878.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they did-- came in from the other side of the city, not from where they're supposed to come from the west.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They came in from the east.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They surrounded the city, surrounded all the old Russian Armies.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they took millions and thousands upon thousands of Russian soldiers and, and PWs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this where I get very upset, when I read a article of a, a German writer-- Aran, Arendt, or something like this.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I forgot her name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she wrote, why didn't the Jewish people stand up and fight against the Germans?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Here is our army of people who had a gun just in their hands.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I saw three Germans.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One German horse in the front, one German to the side, another German on the side on a horse here, leading millions of people and PWs, soldiers.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And not only that, the Germans-- which I'll tell you later after I explain to you about the ghettos-- where the Germans imposed upon us the collective-- the collective punishment.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's not like I saw a demonstration, demonstration in, in, in Warsaw-- in Washington, DC.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the name of the law, please disperse, begging the people to disperse their demonstrating.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Germans wouldn't say 'the name of the law.' The Germans opened up machine guns and, and kill 10,000, 5,000 people on the spot.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, this a collective punishment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In June, the Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As soon as they came in, the Wehrmacht came in, the soldiers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we find that first day, they killed this man, or they killed this man.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A man went out the back of the house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They killed him--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Originally, they apparently cared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They cared from beginning because they had a pact with the Ukrainians, too-- the Germans already.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
